    "lesson_content_markdown":  "# Finished Past: Regular Type\n\nWe use the **Simple Past** to talk about things that happened and finished before now. This is the most common way to talk about the past.\n\n### 1. How to build it\n\nFor most words, you just add **-ed** to the end of the action word.\n\n- **Walk** â†’ **Walked**\n- **Watch** â†’ **Watched**\n- **Finish** â†’ **Finished**\n\n### 2. Spelling Rules\n\n- If the word ends in **-e**, just add **-d**.\n  - Example: **Live** â†’ **Lived**\n- If the word ends in a **Consonant + y**, change the **y** to **i** and add **-ed**.\n  - Example: **Study** â†’ **Studied**\n- If the word is short and ends in a **Vowel + Consonant**, double the last letter.\n  - Example: **Stop** â†’ **Stopped**\n\n### 3. Past Time Words\n\nWe often use these words to show the action is finished:\n- Yesterday\n- Last night / Last week / Last year\n- Two days ago / Three hours ago\n- In 2023\n\n### Examples:\n- I **finished** my homework last night.\n- She **studied** for the test in the library.\n- The students **talked** to the teacher after class.\n- We **watched** a movie in the student lounge yesterday.\n\n---",
